### Continue Workflow Testing - Login as Department Manager
### Test the workflow approval system with proper approver roles

### 1. Login as Department Manager (manager@demo.com)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@demo.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 2. Get Approval Tasks for Department Manager
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Get Approval Tasks assigned to me (department manager)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals?assigned_to_me=true
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Get Pending Approval Tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Get Workflow Status for our test requisition (REQ-260109-14EA)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/documents/REQ-260109-14EA/approval-status
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Get Available Approvers for Requisitions
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals/available-approvers?documentType=REQUISITION
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Approve the workflow task (replace TASK_ID with actual task ID from step 2)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals/TASK_ID/approve
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signature": "manager_digital_signature",
  "comment": "Approved by department manager - requisition meets department requirements"
}

### 8. Check workflow status after approval
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/documents/REQ-260109-14EA/approval-status
Authorization: Bearer MANAGER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 9. Login as Finance User (finance@demo.com) for next stage
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "finance@demo.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 10. Get Approval Tasks for Finance User
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer FINANCE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 11. Approve as Finance User (replace TASK_ID with actual task ID)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals/TASK_ID/approve
Authorization: Bearer FINANCE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signature": "finance_digital_signature",
  "comment": "Approved by finance - budget allocation confirmed"
}

### 12. Check final workflow status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/documents/REQ-260109-14EA/approval-status
Authorization: Bearer FINANCE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 13. Get the final requisition status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/requisitions/REQ-260109-14EA
Authorization: Bearer FINANCE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 14. Login back as Admin to verify requester cannot approve their own requests
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@liyali.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 15. Check if admin can see approval tasks for their own requisition (should be empty)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals?assigned_to_me=true
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 16. Verify admin cannot approve their own requisition
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/documents/REQ-260109-14EA/approval-status
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json